"script": "Could you ever stand on the surface of Jupiter? Here's the twist: there is no surface to stand on. As you fall in, the clouds look solid, but you'd plunge straight through them. Then the winds hit, screaming past at over a thousand miles an hour, faster than any storm on Earth. Keep falling and the gas around you thickens into a hot, crushing soup. The pressure soon grows strong enough to flatten a submarine. And deeper still, the gas turns into liquid metal. You'd never hit ground, because there is none, just an endless fall into a planet with no floor.",
